  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed Senate amended", 
    "date": "1984-02-23", 
    "text": "(Measure passed Senate, amended, roll call #16 (92-0)) Armed Career Criminal Act of 1983 - Amends the Federal criminal code to establish a mandatory sentence of 15 years to life and a fine of not more than $25,000 for \"armed career criminals.\" Applies such penalties to any person with two prior convictions who commits, conspires, or attempts to commit a robbery or burglary while in possession of a firearm. States that it is the intent of Congress that prosecutions under this Act shall take place only where circumstances justify exceptional handling."
  }, 
